# Guerrilla

## Overview

The name "Guerrilla" is the state-of-the-art automation testing platform tailored for hardware. Experience seamless integration and efficient testing workflows, ensuring accuracy and consistency in every step of your process.

ðŸš¸ Documentation still in progress, if you have any questions or ideas, please let us know.  [Docs](https://www.guerrilla.dev/)

## Getting Started

Install guerrilla from pip
```bash
pip install guerrilla
```

```py
from guerrilla.device import Device
config = {
    "name": "EDR-G9010",
    "type": "router",
    "host": "192.168.127.254",
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "moxa",
    "protocol": "ssh",
}
device = Device(config)
device.connect()
```

```zsh
2023-10-30 00:14:07.637 | SUCCESS  | guerrilla.connection.ssh:connect:77 - Connected to EDR-G9010 192.168.127.254:22
```

### Use the utils library
```py
device.show_version()
```
```zsh
2023-10-30 11:16:41.620 | DEBUG    | guerrilla.connection.ssh:run:230 - From EDR-G9010     sent command: show version
2023-10-30 11:16:42.121 | DEBUG    | guerrilla.connection.ssh:run:234 - From EDR-G9010 received  output: show version
Model Name                   : EDR-G9010-VPN-2MGSFP-T
Firmware Version             : V3.2.99 build 23102123
Firewall/VPN Router 00000#
```

### Execute command what you want

```py
device.run('show interfaces wan')
```
```zsh
